        <div class="inner">
          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Culver City, CA</p>
  <h1>IT Security Manager at Riot Games</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>As one of the most popular PC games today, League of Legends is reshaping PC gaming and core gamers perception of virtual goods. Riot Games (named a Top 30 developer by Game Developer Magazine), the publisher and developer of League of Legends, is experiencing a period of rapid growth, doubling the size of the company in the past year. With several million players in their debut title across the US and Europe, and numerous awards (including IGN.com’s Readers' Choice for Best Multiplayer Game for League of Legends), Riot Games has also pioneered innovative marketing for their debut title.</p>

<p>The Information Technology Security Manager position is responsible for managing and overseeing all aspects of security related to the company’s business and online games. The role involves working with Riot’s technology groups, development teams, and partners to develop, implement, maintain, and monitor security policies and procedures.</p>

<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>

<p>•Assist in development of information security policies, standards, procedures, and checklists</p>

<p>•Install, configure, monitor, and respond to network and host based intrusion prevention systems, firewalls, and other security devices</p>

<p>•Respond to and analyze security system alerts and incident reports</p>

<p>•Lead risk analysis of software, systems, and architectures</p>

<p>•Proactively assess potential items of risk and opportunities of vulnerability in the network&amp; systems</p>

<p>•Communicate problems and solutions to peers and management</p>

<p>•Maintain security monitoring, control, and analysis tools</p>

<p>•Manage one to two projects simultaneously and complete them on schedule</p>

<p>•Ensure procedures and processes are clearly and accurately documented and implemented</p>

<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>

<p>•Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or other related field or equivalent knowledge with 8 years of related professional experience, 3 of which were in a supervisory capacity.</p>

<p>•Experience with a broad range of exposure to all aspects of business planning, mission-critical systems, systems analysis and applications is desired.</p>

<p>•In depth knowledge and experience with concepts and issues related to computing and infrastructure security.</p>

<p>•Understand advanced security protocols and standards</p>

<p>•Knowledge and work experience related to the field of security in a computing environment with similar complexity.</p>

<p>•Ability to operate independently, and exercise significant latitude for independent judgment, discretion, and action.</p>

<p>•Ability to train and develop staff.</p>

<p>•Ability to work successfully in a team environment and to form and maintain effective teams.</p>

<p>•Excellent oral and written communication skills with a proven ability to effectively interact with all levels of employees.</p>

<p>•Experience with vulnerability assessment tools, packet analyzers,&amp; security management suites</p>

<p>•Experience with VPN, Firewall, IDS/IPS,&amp; HIDS</p>

<p>•Ability to multi-task and work well under pressure in a fast-paced on-time deliverable environment</p>

<p>•Strong interpersonal and communication skills</p>

<p>•Must be self-motivated and able to work effectively both alone and as part of a team</p>

<p>•Some travel may be required</p>

<p><strong>Preferred:</strong></p>

<p>•Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) and CISCO Certified Security Professional (CSSP) certifications are desired.</p>

<p>•Experience working with Linux and Windows operating systems in production environments</p>

<p>If you are a top-notch Information Technology Security Manager who wants the opportunity to innovate with a creative and talented team and have a positive, “can do” attitude, we want to hear from you!</p>

<p>Riot games is paying salaries that are competitive with the enterprise software industry.</p>

<p>NO RECRUITERS. NO PHONE CALLS. WE DO NOT ACCEPT WALK-INS OR PHONE CALLS TO OUR OFFICE, FAILURE TO FOLLOW THIS DIRECTIVE WILL RESULT IN IMMEDIATE DISQUALIFICATION FROM ANY POSITION AT RIOT GAMES.</p>
</div><!-- /.column.main -->

